                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4280: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-05T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 5, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 5—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>129. Military Attaché who called at War Ministry at 5:30 this afternoon was told
                    officially that the white troops of Marshal Badoglio’s column had reached the
                    outskirts of Addis Ababa and were being organized preparatory to the entry into
                    the city tomorrow morning. Unofficially it was stated that word had been
                    received that an Italian truck column of white soldiers had passed the British
                    Legation outside Addis Ababa on its way to the city and that this column was
                    being sent in advance to restore order.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
